# Email Rules

## Sending Email

- Use `sendEmail({ to, subject, text, html })` from `@/lib/sendgrid-smtp` (or `lib/smtp-mail.ts` if configured).
- All outgoing HTML must use the shared theme so fonts and light/dark mode are consistent.

## Shared Theme (lib/email-theme.ts)

- **getEmailHead()** — Returns `<meta>`, font link (Montserrat), and `<style>` with `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` overrides. Include in every HTML email template.
- **EMAIL.light** — Use for inline styles: `bg: "#f5f1e9"`, `text: "#1c1917"`, `green: "#464C45"`, `cardBg`, `cardBorder`, `deposit`, `danger`, etc.
- **EMAIL.dark** — Used only in the `<style>` block for dark mode; no need to reference in inline HTML.
- **Class names for dark mode:** Add `class="email-body"` on `<body>`, `class="email-wrap"` on main wrapper, `class="email-header"`, `class="email-card"`, `class="email-footer"`, `class="email-notice"`, `class="email-link"`, `class="email-accent-bar"`, `class="email-badge"` so the dark-mode media query can override colors.

## Template Structure (consistent design)

1. `<head>${getEmailHead()}</head>`
2. `<body class="email-body" style="...font-family: ${EMAIL.font}; background: ${L.bg}; color: ${L.text}">`
3. Main wrapper: `<div class="email-wrap" style="max-width:560px; margin:0 auto; background: ${L.wrap}; ...">`
4. Header strip: `<div class="email-header" style="background: ${L.green}; ...">` (title + optional badge)
5. Body: cards with `class="email-card"`, notices with `class="email-notice"`
6. Footer: `<div class="email-footer" style="...">`

## Where Emails Are Sent

- **Bookings:** `app/api/bookings/route.ts` — customer booking confirmation (with payment link); use `generateCustomerBookingConfirmationEmailHtml` + `getEmailHead`/`EMAIL`.
- **Stripe payment confirmed:** `app/api/stripe/confirm-payment/route.ts` — customer payment confirmation + admin "New Paid Booking"; use `generatePaymentConfirmationEmail` and admin HTML with `getEmailHead`/`EMAIL`.
- **Newsletter:** `app/api/newsletter/subscribe/route.ts` — welcome + discount code; use `getEmailHead`/`EMAIL`.
- **Test emails:** `app/api/test-email/route.ts` + `app/api/test-email/templates.ts` — all templates 1:1 with production; use `getTemplate(templateId)` which uses `getEmailHead` and `EMAIL`.
- **Other:** `app/api/admin/discount-codes/route.ts`, `app/api/payments/send-link-email/route.ts`, `app/api/notifications/reminders/route.ts`, `app/api/invoices/[id]/send-email/route.ts` — use same theme when adding or editing.

## Adding a New Email Template

1. In the API route that sends the email, import `getEmailHead` and `EMAIL` from `@/lib/email-theme`.
2. Build HTML with the structure above and inline styles from `EMAIL.light` (e.g. `L = EMAIL.light`).
3. Add classes for dark mode where applicable.
4. If the template is user-facing and should be testable, add a corresponding case in `app/api/test-email/templates.ts` and add the template id to the test-email GET/POST handling.
